CEO observations
DBS Group Holdings
3Q 2024 financial results
November 7, 2024
Disclaimer: The information contained in this document is intended only for use during the presentation and should not be disseminated or distributed to parties outside the presentation.
DBS Bank accepts no liability whatsoever with respect to the use of this document or its contents.

Another record quarterly and nine-month performance

Group NII stable QoQ as balance sheet growth offset lower NIM
Commercial book NIM unchanged, supported by reduced interest rate sensitivity
o
Lower Group NIM due to markets trading’s deployment in products with inherent
o
accounting asymmetry which are accretive to income but dilutive to NIM

Fee income reaches new high
Strong momentum in wealth management
o

Highest markets trading income in ten quarters, capitalised on market volatility

Cost-income ratio stable at 39%

Asset quality resilient, NPL ratio lower
Repayments, recoveries and write-offs more than offset new NPA formation
o

New share buyback programme another affirmation of commitment to capital
management, underpinned by strong capital position and earnings generation
2

2025 outlook

Group net interest income around 2024 levels
Slight decline in Group NIM, mostly offset by loan growth
o
Markets trading to benefit from lower funding cost
o

Commercial book non-interest income growth to be high-single digits
Led by growth in wealth management fees and treasury customer sales
o

Cost-income ratio to be in low-40% range

SP assumed to normalise to 17-20bp, although not seeing signs of stress so far
Potential for GP writebacks
o

Pretax profit to be around 2024 levels

Net profit to be below 2024 levels due to global minimum tax of 15%
3
